The paper presents an algorithm for maintaining a topological order of a directed acyclic graph and detecting cycles as arcs are added. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of median-finding, which is a common technique in computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the maintenance of strong components of a directed graph, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
